Erm, actually, what was required to say that was counting. Not all counting methods are the same, as I could’ve been counting in base10, base20, or even base64. Counting is not the same thing as math because the next number will always be known unlike the answer to any equation, there is work involved to find the answer as it’s how math works. Math wasn’t required to make this statement, but counting was. Counting in base64 is the algorithm minecraft uses for its “item stacks.” After the stack reaches 64, it reverts back to 1 because base64 ends at 64. Basic counting is the only thing that was “required” for this message to exist because ironically math and counting are not the same. ️
